org.dllearner.core
Class ReasoningService

java.lang.Object
  org.dllearner.core.ReasoningService

public class ReasoningService
extends Object

The reasoning service is the interface to the used reasoner. Basically, it delegates all incoming reasoner request to the Reasoner object which has been specified in the constructor. However, it calculates some additional statistics about the time the reasoner needs to answer the query.

Author:
Jens Lehmann

Constructor Detail

ReasoningService

public ReasoningService(ReasonerComponent reasoner)
Constructs a reasoning service object. Note that you must not modify the underlying knowledge base of a reasoning service (if you do, you have to create a new reasoning service object). Further note, that the initialisation is lazy, e.g. you can feed the constructor with a non-initialised reasoner component. However, of course you need to make sure that the resoner component is initialised before the first reasoner query.

reasoner -
